---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Writing"
  description="Reflections on missional design, digital formation, and building technology for human flourishing."
>
  <div class="container">
    <section class="section">
      <h1>Writing</h1>
      <p class="text-muted" style="max-width: none; font-size: 1.1rem;">
        Reflections on missional design, digital formation, and building technology for human flourishing.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="grid grid-2">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Coming soon: The Ministry Model Canvas</h3>
          <p>
            A practical tool for mapping missional product decisions. Using a single-page canvas, teams can align on
            their spiritual formation goals, user assumptions, and the metrics that matter most.
          </p>
          <p class="text-muted" style="font-size: 0.9rem; margin-top: var(--spacing-lg);">Stay tuned</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <h3>Coming soon: Why churches and startups have more in common than you think</h3>
          <p>
            Both are attempting to create sustained communities around a vision. Both struggle with engagement vs. depth.
            Both face the same fundamental tension: how to scale something that requires intimacy?
          </p>
          <p class="text-muted" style="font-size: 0.9rem; margin-top: var(--spacing-lg);">Stay tuned</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section-alt section">
      <div class="container text-center">
        <h2>More content coming soon</h2>
        <p class="text-muted">
          In the meantime, explore the framework above or reach out if you have thoughts to share.
        </p>
        <a href="mailto:hello@treppmann.design" class="btn">Get in Touch</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .card h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .card p {
    flex: 1;
  }
</style>
